**TL;DR — The 7-Step Princess Cut Buying Checklist**

1. **Proportions first:** Table 65–75%, depth 64–75%, L:W 1.00–1.02
2. **Skip the "Ideal" label:** No GIA Excellent exists for princess — evaluate table, depth, polish, and symmetry manually
3. **Color floor — white metal:** G minimum (H shows corner warmth in platinum and white gold)
4. **Color floor — warm metal:** H acceptable in yellow or rose gold (metal masks corner tint)
5. **Clarity floor:** VS1 minimum — corners concentrate inclusions; VS2 requires cert-by-cert review
6. **Setting:** 4 V-prongs on all 4 corners, platinum preferred
7. **Budget split:** ~55% diamond, ~45% setting at the luxury tier; ~70% diamond, ~30% setting under $3,000 total

→ **[Complete Princess Cut Engagement Ring Guide](/princess-cut-diamond-engagement-ring)** — all settings, all metals, size-to-carat chart, and corner protection checklist.

